<b>Mr. H.R.</b>; <b>Ms. M.Z.</b>, a children&#8217;s right activist, the President of the NGO &#8216;Struggle for a 
World Deserving of Children&#8217; and member of the &#8216;One Million Signatures Campaign&#8217;; <b>Mr. 
N.A.</b>, a lawyer representing imprisoned journalists; <b>Mr. M.H.</b>, a journalist working for the 
now closed Etemad-e Melli newspaper and <b>Mr. M.R.Z.</b>, the former editor of the newspaper 
Arya, were arrested between the 27 December 2009 and the 1 of January 2010. According 
to the information received, <b>Ms. N.E.</b>, the sister of the Nobel Peace Prize winner Shirin 
Ebadi, was detained on 28 December 2009 and held at an unknown location. 
